
[Without place] 30 Mch. 1781. Mr. Eppes desires him to inform TJ that a Gun Smith up the Country will undertake the Cleaning and repairing Arms. He will also get 3 or 4 Men to Assist him provided they are exempt from Military duty. The arms must be sent up to him. TJs instructions follow: Referred to Colo. Davies; Colo. Muter had the name of this man in a note from me. He lives in Cumberland on Appomattox. Th:J.
